stixCommon:Identity.stixCommon:Name: This report contains Indicators of Compromise (IOC) identified by opening or executing malicious files in a dynamic malware analysis sandbox. The hostnames were extracted from the sandbox's network activity and validated against the following rules: Must not be in the Alexa 1 Million, Must have a valid Top Level Domain. These steps may not prevent legitimate hostnames from being included in these IOCs. However, if the IOCs include legitimate hostnames it means they are either compromised and used as accessory to malicious activities or used to evade dynamic analysis environments such as Internet connectivity checks. It is left to the recipient to evaluate the impact of blocking access to these sites. Please e-mail CCCS (contact@cyber.gc.ca) with any questions you may have related to the data in this report.
